HEADWORD: Ology
<hw>Ol"o*gy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>-logy</er>.]</ety> <def>A colloquial or humorous name for any
science or branch of knowledge.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He had a smattering of mechanics, of physiology, geology,
mineralogy, and all other <qex>ologies</qex> whatsoever.</q> <rj><qau>De
Quincey.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Olpe</ent>⟦br⟧
